  "text": "Concerning the EI, results showed a similar trend on the perception between PSA kind and Gender, where women showed a negative emotional involvement when exposed to Effective PSAs, while men showed a slightly positive emotional involvement. Statistical results highlighted a significant difference for Effective antismoking images between females and males (p � 0.014), according to literature, which highlighted a gender difference on the appreciation of TV advertisements [CITATION_1] , and how women are more influenced by advertisement that emphasize the health effects of smoking [CITATION_2] . ese researches showed that women seem generally influenced by antismoking PSAs, causing a more negative emotional involvement with respect to men. Furthermore, the lowest EI value for women reported in this study could be mainly explained by one of two Effective images, depicting a sick lady presenting the signs of a tracheotomy.",
